o made significant and influential interventions in the field. Sexual Politics and Feminist Science provides readers with an opportunity to rediscover and engage with the work of these pioneers.Leng highlights sexology's empowering potential for women, but also contends that in its intersection with eugenics, the narrative is not wholly celebratory. By detailing gendered efforts to understand and theorize sex through science, she reveals the cognitive biases and sociological prejudices that ultimately circumscribed the transformative potential of their ideas. Ultimately, Sexual Politics and Feminist Science helps readers to understand these women's ideas in all their complexity in order to appreciate their unique place in the history of sexology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aElectronic books. 0aFeminism and sciencexHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aFeminism and sciencezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aFeministsxHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aFeministszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex rolexHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aSex rolezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aSexologyxHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aSexologyzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen sexologistsxHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aWomen sexologistszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxSexual behaviorxHistoryy20th centuryzGermany. 0aWomenxSexual behaviorzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 4aGERMAN STUDIES. 4aHistory. 4aWomens Studies. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  agender politics, sexology, Mathilde Vaerting, Social Justice, Meisel-Hess, First World War, Sofie Lazarsfeld.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060